Average size of the C-dots was found to be 4.3nm, as confirmed by the statistical analysis of more than 100C-dots observed in TEM image and height profile of the AFM image (Fig. 1

                     ). The three peaks at 283.0, 397.0 and 531.5eV in XPS spectrum [34] (Fig. 2

                     ) can be attributed to C1s, N1s and O1s, respectively suggesting that the synthesized C-dots contained C, O and N with% atom ratio of C:O:N=58.64: 34.89: 6.47. The three peaks in the high resolution XPS of C1s spectrum at 283.1, 285.2 and 286.7eV are assigned to CC, CN and CO, respectively. The two peaks at 531.3 and 531.9eV in O1s spectrum are assigned to CO and COH/COC groups, while the two peaks at 398.5 and 400.2eV in N1s spectrum are assigned to the CNC and NH groups, respectively. The N contained in the C-dots comes from the precursor. The Zeta Potential of the synthesized C-dots was found to be −21.5mV. The peaks at 1644 and 1308cm−1 in the FTIR spectrum (Fig. 3
                     a) suggesting the presence of CO stretching and COOH stretching. Peaks at 2922 and 995cm−1 shows the CH stretching and bending respectively and the broad peak at 3295cm−1 is attributed to OH and NH stretching vibrations. This result provides the evidence that oxygen containing functional groups, especially OH and COOH are majorly present in the C-dots.
